# {{ project_name }}

Flutter {{ "3.22+" }} cross-platform app rendered from OmniSight
SKILL-FLUTTER (P9 #294). One Dart codebase, both stores.

## Platform targets

| Store         | Profile                                      | Build command                          |
|---------------|----------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|
| App Store     | `configs/platforms/ios-arm64.yaml`           | `flutter build ipa --release`          |
| Google Play   | `configs/platforms/android-arm64-v8a.yaml`   | `flutter build appbundle --release`    |

Deployment floors (pinned from P0 profiles, not copied):

- iOS: `min_os_version = {{ min_os_version_ios }}` (StoreKit 2 baseline).
- Android: `minSdk = {{ min_os_version_android }}`, `targetSdk = {{ sdk_version_android }}`.

## Running locally

```sh
flutter pub get
cd ios && pod install && cd ..
flutter run -d <device-id>        # picks an iOS sim or Android AVD
```

## Testing

```sh
flutter test --coverage           # unit + widget tests
flutter test integration_test/    # integration test via P2 simulate-track
```

The P2 simulate-track `run_flutter_tests` runner invokes
`flutter test integration_test --reporter=json` — the scaffold is
compatible out-of-the-box.

## Signing

NEVER commit keystores or provisioning profiles. Everything goes
through `OMNISIGHT_*` env vars sourced from `backend/secret_store` at
build time (P3 chain). See `android/key.properties.example` for the
expected env-ref shape.

## Package id

`{{ package_id }}` is shared between iOS `CFBundleIdentifier` and
Android `applicationId` — the whole point of cross-platform is one id
per product. Change the id via `render_project(... package_id=...)`.
